ra%20of%20rearmament%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20it's%20learning%20it%20needs%20to%20invest%20in%20technology%20it%20previously%20thought%20would%20be%20redundant%20in%20fast-moving%2C%20tech-heavy%20wars%20they%20envisaged%20would%20define%20the%2021st%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20has%20used%20mines%20to%20slow%20the%20larger%20Russian%20army's%20advances%20in%20the%20east%20and%20south%20of%20the%20country%20to%20a%20stalemate%20and%20to%20channel%20enemy%20troops%20into%20areas%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20its%20forces%20can%20defend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20sophisticated%20precision-guided%20missiles%20NATO%20has%20provided%20Ukraine%20are%20susceptible%20to%20Russian%20electronic%20jamming%20that%20scrambles%20the%20signals%20used%20to%20guide%20them%2C%20comparatively%20crude%20%E2%80%94%20and%20cheap%20%E2%80%94%20shells%20don't%20have%20this%20drawback.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine's%20European%20allies%20have%20boosted%20shell%20production.%20But%20last%20week%2C%20NATO's%20supreme%20allied%20commander%20in%20Europe%2C%20US%20Army%20Gen.%20Christopher%20Cavoli%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-artillery-ammo-stockpile-triple-us-europe-combined-chris-cavoli-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20the%20Senate%20Armed%20Services%20Committee%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Russia%20was%20on%20track%20to%20build%20a%20shell%20stockpile%20%26quot%3Bthree%20times%20greater%20than%20the%20United%20States%20and%20Europe%20combined.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20paper%2C%20the%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%2C%20a%20UK%20defense%20think%20tank%2C%20said%20European%20governments%20had%20expected%20private%20sector%20defense%20firms%20to%20%26quot%3Bsolve%20the%20problem%26quot%3B%20of%20ammunition%20production%20but%20failed%20to%20introduce%20%26quot%3Bany%20incentives%20or%20a%20regulatory%20environment%20that%20would%20allow%20it%20to%20do%20so.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2242c7d1b2-edeb-46c1-bae2-9cc987afe2fa%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENato%20had%20been%20planning%20for%20a%20different%20war%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPaul%20van%20Hooft%2C%20a%20defense%20research%20leader%20at%20the%20UK-based%20think%20tank%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ERAND%20Europe%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20threat%20from%20Russia%20was%20very%20different%20from%20what%20Western%20military%20leaders%20had%20planned%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20three%20decades%2C%20as%20Western%20militaries%20were%20not%20focused%20on%20large-scale%20land%20warfare%20and%20territorial-NATO%20collective%20defense%2C%20these%20weapons%20%5Bsuch%20as%20shells%20and%20land%20mines%5D%20were%20not%20considered%20as%20valuable%20%E2%80%94%20specifically%20in%20Western%20Europe%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI%20by%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%209%2F11%20attacks%2C%20NATO%20allies%20planned%20for%20wars%20against%20militias%20such%20as%20the%20Taliban%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20where%20land%20mines%20and%20shells%20had%20little%20obvious%20use%2C%20said%20van%20Hooft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20fighting%20a%20land%20war%20against%20a%20large%20army%20requires%20defending%20and%20holding%20large%20swaths%20of%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArtillery%20may%20be%20old%20technology%20but%20it's%20more%20effective%20when%20used%20alongside%20newer%20surveillance%20tech%20like%20drones%2C%20said%20Van%20Hooft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Cancian%2C%20a%20senior%20advisor%20with%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%20Defense%20and%20Security%20Department%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20said%20that%20as%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20has%20become%20more%20static%2C%20shells%20and%20land%20mines%20have%20once%20again%20been%20proven%20indispensable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20weapons%20become%20useful%2C%20even%20dominant%2C%20whenever%20the%20front%20lines%20stabilize%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20are%20difficult%20to%20employ%20when%20armies%20are%20maneuvering%20but%20easy%20to%20employ%20when%20armies%20stalemate%20and%20dig%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Ukraine%2C%20drones%20have%20been%20used%20to%20surveil%20battlefields%2C%20identify%20troops%20gatherings%20or%20command%20posts%20%E2%80%94%20and%20pinpoint%20positions%20to%20target%20with%20artillery%20barrages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECancian%20cautioned%20against%20military%20planners%20becoming%20%26quot%3Benamored%20with%20flashy%20concepts%20of%20future%20warfare%26quot%3B%20as%20billions%20are%20poured%20into%20European%20defense%20budgets%20and%20military%20tech%20startups%20compete%20for%20business%20selling%20cutting-edge%20drones%20and%20AI-integrated%20weapons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BArtillery-firing%2C%20unguided%20munitions%20are%20still%20critical%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BNotions%20that%20the%20next%20war%20would%20be%20fought%20by%20small%20teams%20firing%20precision%20munitions%20has%20not%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20the%20case.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fland-mines-artillery-shells-ukraine-nato-europe-defense-russia-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744192829000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f3cca563d72727e1995a2b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fland-mines-artillery-shells-ukraine-nato-europe-defense-russia-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Land%20mines%20and%20artillery%20shells%20have%20proven%20essential%20weapons%20for%20Ukraine%2C%20and%20NATO%20is%20taking%20note.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tporter%40businessinsider.com%20(Tom%20Porter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A14%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fland-mines-artillery-shells-ukraine-nato-europe-defense-russia-2025-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20much%20will%20your