s%20offering%20tech%20help%20for%20boomers%20for%20%2450%20an%20hour.%20This%20image%20has%20been%20edited%20to%20omit%20his%20contact%20details.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Madison%20St.%20Onge%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EErik%20Boquist%2C%2027%2C%20has%20made%20a%20side%20gig%20out%20of%20helping%20older%20adults%20improve%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-looking-for-work-you-should-volunteer-job-recruiter-says-2024-7%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etech%20skills%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20charges%20%2450%20an%20hour%2C%20offering%20personalized%20guidance.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBoquist%20said%20he%20enjoys%20the%20work%20because%20the%20older%20people%20he%20helps%20are%20grateful%20and%20%26quot%3Bso%20sharp.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Erik%20Boquist%2C%2027%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Sutton%2C%20New%20Hampshire%2C%20and%20travels%20the%20US%20and%20beyond%20working%20as%20a%20house-sitter%20with%20his%20girlfriend.%20Boquist%20also%20does%20video%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fitsnow.co%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eediting%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20His%20latest%20side%20gig%20is%20showing%20people%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20are%20older%2C%20how%20to%20level%20up%20their%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-people-struggling-new-technology-aging-parents-kids-assistance-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Etech%20skills%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20his%20identity%20and%20that%20Boquist%20has%20earned%20money%20from%20these%20efforts.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20brevity%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20thinking%20about%20training%20baby%20boomers%20on%20technology%20because%20of%20the%20simple%20tech%20tasks%20my%20mom%20needs%20help%20with%20and%20because%20I%20saw%20glimpses%20of%20my%20dad's%20workflow.%20Those%20were%20huge%20revelations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20everything%20from%20how%20they%20email%2C%20surf%20the%20web%2C%20and%20watch%20videos%20on%20YouTube.%20There%20might%20be%20simple%20things%20they%20don't%20know%20about%2C%20like%20changing%20the%20playback%20speed%20or%20using%20the%20arrows%20to%20go%20ahead%20or%20back%20five%20seconds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mother%20lives%20in%20a%2055-plus%20community%2C%20and%20one%20day%2C%20after%20helping%20her%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BErik%2C%20you%20should%20be%20doing%20this%20for%20everybody%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoom.%20She%20was%20right.%20If%20I'm%20going%20to%20help%20the%20community%20as%20much%20as%20possible%2C%20I%20just%20have%20to%20let%20people%20know%20I%20would%20be%20willing%20to%20talk%20with%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20role%20is%20often%20vetting%20what%20they're%20hearing%20and%20then%20making%20money%20off%20researching%20it%20and%20determining%20if%20it's%20legit.%20It%20might%20be%20simple%20things%20like%20someone%20wanting%20a%20box%20of%20markers%20to%20do%20crafts.%20I%20ask%20whether%20they've%20thought%20about%20Amazon%20and%20whether%20they%20have%20an%20account.%20If%20not%2C%20I%20might%20help%20them%20set%20it%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20want%20the%20people%20I'm%20helping%20to%20realize%20that%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20they're%20able-bodied%20or%20not%2C%20they%20just%20need%20to%20be%20able%20to%20use%20their%20fingers.%20Dude%2C%20they're%20so%20sharp.%20You%20talk%20to%20somebody%20who's%2080%20years%20old%20%E2%80%94%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20generalize%2C%20but%20I'm%20going%20to%20generalize%20%E2%80%94%20they%20can%20do%20what%20younger%20people%20can%20do%20on%20computers.%20I%20don't%20want%20older%20people's%20voices%20to%20be%20lost%2C%20the%20wisdom%20to%20be%20lost.%20I%20want%20them%20to%20express%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20doing%20this%20for%20about%20six%20months.%20One%20of%20the%20things%20I'm%20working%20on%20now%20is%20digitizing%20the%20journals%20written%20by%20a%20woman's%20brother%20who%20passed%20away.%20The%20journals%20span%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20wants%20to%20get%20them%20into%20a%20PDF%20that%20can%20be%20shared%20with%20his%20friends.%20We're%20also%20thinking%20of%20using%20AI%20to%20create%20an%20audio%20recording%20of%20the%20entries.%20This%20can%20bring%20more%20remembrance%20of%20her%20brother's%20life%20and%20experiences%20because%20they're%20fascinating%20stories%2C%20and%20his%20voice%20is%20so%20interesting.%20Once%20it's%20digitized%2C%20she%20can%20even%20then%20play%20with%20text%20and%20make%20songs%20from%20the%20journal%20entries%20using%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20I%20sit%20down%20with%20people%2C%20usually%20IRL%2C%20and%20ask%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20do%20you%20want%20to%20do%3F%20What%20have%20you%20heard%20that%20interests%20you%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOutside%20my%20parents%2C%20the%20first%20person%20I%20helped%20was%20my%20neighbor%2C%20who%20I%20always%20saw%20walking%20her%20dog.%20I%20was%20chatting%20with%20her%2C%20and%20she%20shared%20that%20she%20couldn't%20listen%20to%20audiobooks%20at%20night%2C%20which%20she%20had%20liked%20to%20do%2C%20because%20the%20battery%20on%20her%20phone%20kept%20dying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20on%20YouTube%20and%20used%20various%20search%20engines.%20The%20question%20became%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20do%20I%20replace%20a%20battery%20for%20an%20iPhone%207%3F%26quot%3B%20She's%20using%20an%20older%20phone%2C%20but%20it%20works%20for%20her.%20I'm%20not%20trying%20to%20sell%20her%20on%20a%20new%20one.%20Some%20of%20the%20reviews%20on%20battery-replacement%20kits%20were%20that%20the%20battery%20died%2030%20days%20after%20they%20were%20replaced.%20So%2C%20I%20suggested%20she%20avoid%20one%20seller%2C%20who%20was%20cheaper%2C%20and%20maybe%20go%20with%20an%20authorized%20battery%20replacer%2C%20who%20was%20%2490.%20She%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20that's%20so%20great%20to%20know%20all%20this.%20Thank%20you%20so%20much.%20Let%20me%20pay%20you%20for%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20told%20her%20no%20because%20it%20was%20a%20great%20lesson%20for%20me.%20That%20was%20the%20start%20of%20realizing%2C%20%26quot%3BWow%2C%20that%20took%20me%20about%2015%20minutes.%26quot%3B%20Then%20I%20shared%20all%20that%20with%20her%20in%20about%2060%20seconds%2C%20and%20it%20seemed%20to%20really%20impact%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20business%20is%20essentially%20demystifying%20tech%20and%20bringing%20more%20knowledge%20to%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20a%20great%20addition%20to%20my%20workflow.%20In%20recent%20months%2C%20I%20had%20three%20consistent%20clients.%20We%20talk%20about%20an%20hour%20at%20a%20time.%20It's%20not%20a%2040-hour%20workweek%20by%20any%20means%2C%20but%20it's%20meaningful.%20So%20it's%20been%20four%20to%2012%20hours%20a%20week%20since%20I%20started%2C%20and%20I%20love%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20fee%20is%20%2450%20an%20hour%2C%20and%20I%20haven't%20had%20the%20heart%20to%20bump%20it%20up.%20People%20are%20OK%20paying%20for%20it.%20Those%20who%20have%20called%20have%20been%20so%20enthusiastic.%20They're%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%20my%20gosh%2C%20I%20wish%20that%20somebody%20had%20been%20doing%20the%20sooner.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20client%20surprises%20me.%20Someone%20might%20say%20something%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20hear%20Bluesky%20is%20the%20opposite%20of%20X.%26quot%3B%20Just%20hearing%20that%20brought%20me%20to%20dive%20deeper%20into%20that%20comparison.%20It's%20fascinating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20girlfriend%20and%20I%20are%20heading%20to%20Seattle%20soon%20to%20house-sit%20for%20a%20family%20with%20a%20pair%20of%20beagles.%20We've%20been%20doing%20it%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20now.%20There%20are%20coffee%20shops%20a%20two-minute%20walk%20from%20the%20place.%20I'll%20put%20up%20flyers%20there%20and%20at%20the%20grocery%20store%2C%20and%20we'll%20see%20what%20rolls%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20had%20sessions%20on%20FaceTime%2C%20but%20when%20I'm%20in%20person%2C%20people%20seem%20more%20likely%20to%20ask%20if%20I%20can%20come%20back%20the%20next%20week.%20Then%2C%20one%20of%20the%20things%20we%20work%20on%20is%20to%20go%20from%20cash%20or%20check%20to%20Venmo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-worker-charges-older-people-tech-support-side-gig-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744190222000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f59f2b3fe8d39283628308%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-worker-charges-older-people-tech-support-side-gig-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Erik%20Boquist%2C%2027%2C%20charges%20%2450%20an%20hour%20to%20teach%20older%20adults%20tech%20skills%2C%20helping%20them%20navigate%20technology%20and%20social%20media%20with%20personalized%20guidance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-worker-charges-older-people-tech-support-side-gig-2025-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I'm%20a%20founder%20who%20moved%20from%20Canada%20to%20the%20US.%20I%20feel%20like%20a%20small%20fish%20in%20the%20American%20market%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20think%20that's%20a%20bad%20thing.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221524%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Left%3A%20Miles%20Schwartz%20working%20at%20an%20outdoor%20table%20with%20a%20laptop%20in%20front%20of%20him%3B%20Right%3A%20The%20Miami%20skyline%20with%20two%20palm%20trees%20in%20front%20of%20it%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f634fc3fe8d392836287b2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22762%5C%22%3E%3Cfigc