-florida-leaving-canada-cant-work-happier-healthier-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoved%20from%20Canada%20to%20Florida%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20lead%20a%20US%20expansion%20effort%20for%20Z%C5%ABm%20Rails.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20found%20that%20the%20US%20market%20is%20much%20bigger%20and%20more%20competitive%20than%20it%20is%20in%20Canada%2C%20which%20puts%20us%20in%20better%20stead%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartups-most-likely-to-become-tech-next-unicorns-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecome%20a%20unicorn%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%20one%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228d17bab2-b8f5-49d9-8673-d7beb9b6765c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20moved%20to%20Miami%20in%20response%20to%20the%20demand%20for%20our%20services%20from%20US%20clients%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20impetus%20to%20expand%20into%20the%20US%20came%20a%20few%20years%20ago%20when%20some%20of%20our%20large%20SaaS%20partners%20told%20us%20that%20they%20needed%20something%20like%20us%20in%20the%20US.%20These%20partners%2C%20who%20have%20a%20presence%20in%20both%20countries%2C%20said%20they'd%20definitely%20use%20us%20if%20we%20had%20a%20US%20presence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20started%20working%20on%20the%20expansion%20in%202022%2C%20and%20spent%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20on%20back-end%20work%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhere-is-the-best-state-to-incorporate-your-business-2011-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincorporating%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20initially%20hired%20a%20professional%20to%20help%20us%20expand.%20As%20time%20went%20on%2C%20the%20work%20felt%20too%20critical%20to%20delegate%2C%20and%20it%20was%20better%20for%20my%20CTO%20and%20I%20to%20move%20to%20Miami%2C%20where%20several%20fintech%20companies%20we'd%20connected%20with%20also%20had%20offices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%3Cem%3E'%3C%2Fem%3Em%20not%20one%20to%20overthink%20a%20decision.%20Within%20a%20few%20weeks%20of%20starting%20to%20consider%20the%20move%2C%20I%20found%20a%20place%20and%20secured%20an%20L1-A%20visa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20in%20Miami%20since%20September%202024.%20Since%20my%20previous%20fintech%20experience%20was%20based%20in%20Canada%2C%20scaling%20our%20operation%20in%20the%20US%20has%20been%20a%20learning%20curve.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229c0d3913-12ed-4970-aa96-6602870a2e4f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHaving%20my%20boots%20on%20the%20ground%20in%20the%20US%20has%20been%20helpful%20for%20business%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20our%20team%20are%20based%20in%20Canada.%20Though%20we%20have%20coworking%20spaces%20in%20Canada%20and%20Florida%2C%20we've%20always%20been%20remote%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20advantages%20of%20being%20in%20Miami%20instead%20of%20Canada.%20I%20wanted%20our%20existing%20clients%20to%20know%20we're%20commited%20to%20our%20US%20expansion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20optics%2C%20I%20think%20people%20take%20you%20more%20seriously%20if%20you're%20based%20in%20the%20US.%20The%20fintech%20scene%20in%20Montreal%20wasn't%20as%20lively%20and%20none%20of%20our%20clients%20were%20based%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20always%20hosting%20clients%20here%2C%20which%20helps%20form%20deeper%20connections.%20I%20chose%20to%20live%20in%20an%20affluent%20area%20to%20meet%20potential%20business%20connections.%20It's%20like%20I'm%20at%20a%20country%20club%20or%20conference%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20happier%20living%20in%20Miami%2C%20which%20makes%20me%20more%20efficient.%20I%20live%20near%20the%20beach%2C%20where%20I%20can%20swim%20and%20walk%20my%20dog.%20In%20Montreal%2C%20during%20the%20winter%2C%20the%20snow%20and%20cold%20made%20even%20simple%20things%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20haven't%20been%20back%20to%20Canada%20since%20I%20moved%2C%20but%20I%20plan%20to%20visit%20this%20summer.%20My%20goal%20is%20to%20bring%20my%20family%20to%20the%20US%20with%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20so%20focused%20on%20my%20work%20that%20I%20don't%20pay%20attention%20to%20political%20drama.%20Fortunately%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrumps-tariffs-highest-since-the-great-depression-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump's%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20don't%20affect%20us%2C%20but%20looking%20back%2C%20I%20think%20we%20moved%20at%20a%20good%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226e9d6445-02cf-4c1b-b819-615e3356a0b1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20US%20ecosystem%20is%20bigger%20and%20more%20competitive%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20fintech%20ecosystem%20is%20bigger%20and%20more%20entrepreneurial%20than%20Canada's.%20Banks%20here%20want%20to%20innovate%20because%20it's%20a%20dog-eat-dog%20competition.%20Meanwhile%2C%20in%20Canada%2C%20there%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-banking-tech-spend-report%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efive%20big%20banks%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20seem%20comfortable%20with%20their%20market%20share.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-banks%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBanks%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20more%20excited%20to%20talk%20to%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20Z%C5%ABm%20Rails%20was%20very%20well%20known%20in%20Canada%2C%20but%20in%20the%20US%2C%20I%20feel%20like%20a%20small%20fish.%20I%20like%20being%20the%20underdog.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaking%20it%20in%20the%20US%20means%20you've%20really%20made%20it.%20But%20the%20competition%20does%20make%20it%20harder%20to%20succeed.%20You%20need%20to%20find%20a%20specific%20niche%2C%20which%20has%20been%20a%20learning%20curve%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20planning%20a%20big%20hiring%20push%20in%20the%20US%2C%20but%20our%20brand%20isn't%20big%20enough%20yet%20to%20attract%20the%20talent%20we%20need.%20We%20have%20a%20great%20Canadian%20team%2C%20but%20the%20US%20is%20more%20competitive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3