or%20you%20to%20get%20the%20hell%20out%20of%20there%20as%20soon%20as%20you%20can%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhluktenko%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20Ukrainian%20drone%20operator%2C%20who%20spoke%20to%20BI%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%2C%20said%20that%20the%20fake%20bunkers%20are%20something%20that%20Ukrainian%20operators%20will%20try%20to%20do%20when%20they%20have%20enough%20personnel%20to%20pull%20it%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227e985a38-ec31-49eb-aebb-785efb176394%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHiding%20from%20the%20eyes%20of%20the%20enemy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcombat-drone-pilot-trainer-russia-ukraine-war-music-background-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrone%20operators%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20high-priority%20targets%20for%20Russia's%20military.%20For%20that%20reason%2C%20they%20regularly%20to%20try%20to%20stay%20concealed%20from%20Russia's%20attack%20drones%20and%20its%20reconnaissance%20drones%20that%20provide%20targeting%20data%20for%20its%20soldiers%20and%20other%20weaponry%2C%20but%20they%20can't%20shy%20away%20from%20the%20front%20lines.%20They%20have%20to%20be%20close%20enough%20to%20fight%2C%20especially%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-electronic-warfare-shows-us-needs-for-future-wars-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimpediments%20like%20electronic%20warfare%3C%2Fa%3E%20covering%20parts%20of%20the%20battlefield%20and%20complicating%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drone%20operator%20who%20requested%20anonymity%20said%20that%20the%20distance%20that%20an%20operator%20can%20hang%20back%20from%20the%20fighting%20depends%20on%20the%20terrain%2C%20but%20operators%20typically%20have%20to%20get%20as%20close%20as%200.9%20miles%20from%20the%20front%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20largely%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussian-war-advances-slow-ukraine-november-march-analysis-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatic%20lines%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20many%20places%20and%20intense%20fighting%2C%20operators%20often%20hide%20underground.%20A%20US%20veteran%20who%20is%20now%20fighting%20for%20Ukraine%20told%20BI%20last%20year%20that%20when%20operating%20from%20a%20town%2C%20most%2C%20if%20not%20all%2C%20of%20the%20buildings%20there%20are%20destroyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20somewhat%20urban%20environment%20is%20all%20rubble%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Men%20in%20camouflage%20gear%20sit%20in%20a%20dark%20room%20lined%20with%20black%20plastic%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f51f9ba466d2b74ab2845b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20soldiers%20rest%20in%20an%20underground%20shelter%20at%20their%20mortar%20position%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20Pokrovsk%2C%20Donetsk%20Oblast%2C%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EDiego%20Herrera%20Carcedo%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20front%20lines%20can%20be%20so%20unmoving%20that%20positions%20get%20%26quot%3Bhit%20enough%20by%20artillery%2C%20drones%2C%20mortars%2C%20and%20other%20types%20of%20ordinance.%20It%20just%20falls%20apart%20little%20by%20little%20by%20little%20over%20time.%20And%20then%20eventually%2C%20it%20gets%20to%20a%20point%20where%20it's%20not%20a%20defendable%20position%2C%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20veteran%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20Ukrainians%2C%20many%20of%20their%20positions%20get%20%26quot%3Bwhittled%20down%20to%20next%20to%20nothing%26quot%3B%20and%20become%20%26quot%3Bimpossible%20to%20defend.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhluktenko%2C%20who%20has%20operated%20both%20strike%20and%20reconnaissance%20drones%2C%20said%20that%20operators%20like%20him%20often%20use%20underground%20dugouts%20covered%20with%20trees%20and%20branches.%20They%20put%20their%20computers%20and